> ## Mud Elemental
>*Large Elemental, neutral evil*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 15
> - **Hit Points** 60 (7d12+15)
> - **Speed** 20ft., swim 40ft.
>___
>|STR|DEX|CON|INT|WIS|CHA|
>|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
>|18 (+4)|8 (-1)|16 (+3)|6 (-2)|10 (+0)|3 (-4)|
>___
> - **Damage Immunities** Poison
> - **Damage Resistance** Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing From Nonmagical Weapons; Lightning
> - **Condition Immunities** Poisoned
> - **Senses** passive Perception 10, Tremorsense 60ft.
> - **Languages** Aquan, Terran
> - **Challenge** 2 (450 XP)
> ___
> ***False Appearance.*** While the Mud Elemental remains motionless, it is indistinguishable from an ordinary mound of mud.
> ### Actions
> ***Slam.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:*  +5 to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. *Hit:* 14 (3d6 + 4) bludgeoning damage.
>
> ***Mud Belch (Recharge 6).***  The Mud Elemental belches viscid mud onto one creature within 5 feet of it. If the target is Medium or smaller, it must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or be restrained for 1 minute. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.


\page
___
> ## Gas Elemental
>*Lare Elemental, neutral*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 14
> - **Hit Points** 40 (4d12+14)
> - **Speed** 20 ft., fly 30 ft.
>___
>|STR|DEX|CON|INT|WIS|CHA|
>|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
>|8 (-1)|12 (+1)|14 (+2)|4 (-3)|10 (+0)|4 (-3)|
>___
> - **Vulnerabilities** Fire
> - **Damage Immunities** Poison
> - **Damage Resistance** Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing From Nonmagical Weapons
> - **Condition Immunities** Poisoned
> - **Senses** passive Perception 10
> - **Languages** Auran
> - **Challenge** 1 (200 XP)
> ___
> ### Actions
> ***Emit Gas.*** The Gas Elemental spews a sphere of colored gas from itself, filling a 20-foot-radius for 1 minute or until dispersed.  The effects non-Elemental creatures in the area suffer depends on the gas colors listed below:
> * *Green:* Creatures must succeed on a DC 11 Constitution saving throw or fall unconscious
> * *Yellow:*  Creatures must succeed on a DC 13 Constitution saving throw or suffer 10 (3d6) poison damage
> * Purple: Creatures must succeed on a DC 13 Wisdom saving throw or fall prone and become incapacitated.  At the end of each of its turns, and each time it takes damage, the creature can make another Wisdom save.
> * White: Creatures in the area are heavily obscured.
> * Black: Creatures must succeed on a DC 11 Wisdom saving throw or suffer one of the following effects at the beginning of each of its turns:
>
>| d10 | Behavior |
|:---:|:-------------|
| 1  | The creature runs in a random direction.  Use a d8 to determine direction.  The creature takes no other actions this turn |
| 2-6  | The creature doesn't move or take an action this turn |
| 7-9 | The creature attempts to attack a random creature within its reach.  If there is no creature within reach, it does nothing this turn|
| 10 | The creature can act and move as normal|
> At the end of each of its turns, and each time it takes damage, the creature can make another Wisdom save.

___
